SIMPLE: effuse
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Effuse
<hw>Ef*fuse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>effusus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>effundere</ets> to pour out;
<ets>ex</ets> + <ets>fundere</ets> to pour. See <er>Fuse</er> to
melt.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Poured out freely; profuse.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So should our joy be very <qex>effuse</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disposed to pour out freely; prodigal.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Spreading loosely, especially on
one side; <as>as, an <ex>effuse</ex> inflorescence</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Loudon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>Having the lips, or edges, of
the aperture abruptly spreading; -- said of certain shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Effuse
<hw>Ef*fuse"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Effusion; loss.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Much
<xex>effuse</xex> of blood.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Effuse
<hw>Ef*fuse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Effused</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Effusing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To pour out like a stream or
freely; to cause to exude; to shed.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With gushing blood <qex>effused</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Effuse
<hw>Ef*fuse"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To emanate; to issue.</def>
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effusion</ent>⟦br⟧
